            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-16 16:31:23" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to deny any relationship of association with someone</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to deny</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages one may best translate ‘deny’ as ‘to make manifest not to know.’ Accordingly, one may translate the first part of {S:04201200900006} as ‘whoever shows people that he does not know me’ or ‘whoever refuses to admit that he does know me.’ Denial need not involve some verbal formulation, though in some languages this is the most common practice. See also {D:33.277}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
